casebody.data:
Office of Disciplinary Counsel v. Dahling.

[Cite as Disciplinary Counsel v. Dahling (2000), 90 Ohio St.3d 246.]

(No. 00-758 Submitted July 6, 2000 Decided October 25, 2000.) *247Jonathan E. Coughlan, Disciplinary Counsel, and Kevin L. Williams, Assistant Disciplinary Counsel, for relator. Per Curiam.

We adopt the findings, conclusions, and recommendation of the board. Respondent is permanently disbarred from the practice of law in Ohio. Costs are taxed to respondent.

Judgment accordingly.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer, Cook and Lundberg Stratton, JJ., concur.
